description.narrative: All country offices in MENA demonstrate enhanced capacities to design and report on risk-informed, equity-focussed and RBM- consistent programmes, which aligned to the Strategic Plan and apply UNICEF programme policies and guidance, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Technical Excellence In Evaluation, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF in the Middle East and North Africa demonstrates strengthened programming excellence for at-scale results for children.

description.narrative: In 2021, the Regional Office (RO) finalized the 2022–2025 Regional Office Management Plan articulating the link between regional accelerators and the Strategic Plan. The RO promoted the digitalization of partnership management and programme monitoring by strengthening the use of eTools in the region. It also provided technical support to the country offices (COs) forthe United Nations Sustainable Development Cooperation Framework and Common Country Assessment development, development and extension of country;programme;documents (CPDs), enhancement of the application of rights- and results-based management principles, and alignment with the UNICEF Strategic Plan. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/03/2022
